  1<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

  3<!--
  4   The XML configuration file is validated against schema file IoC.Configuration.Schema.7579ADB2-0FBD-4210-A8CA-EE4B4646DB3F.xsd,
  5   which can be found in folder IoC.Configuration.Content in output directory.
  6   The schema file can also be downloaded from
  7   http://oroptimizer.com/ioc.configuration/V2/IoC.Configuration.Schema.7579ADB2-0FBD-4210-A8CA-EE4B4646DB3F.xsd or in source code
  8   project in Github.com.
  9
 10   To use Visual Studio code completion based on schema contents, right click Properties on this file in Visual Studio, and in Schemas
 11   field pick the schema IoC.Configuration.Schema.7579ADB2-0FBD-4210-A8CA-EE4B4646DB3F.xsd.
 12
 13   Before running the tests make sure to execute IoC.Configuration\Tests\IoC.Configuration.Tests\PostBuildCommands.bat to copy the dlls into
 14   folders specified in this configuration file.
 15   Also, modify the batch file to copy the Autofac and Ninject assemblies from Nuget packages folder on machine, where the test is run.
 16-->
 17

124  <!--
125    If settingsRequestor element is used, the type in type attribute should
126    specify a type that implements IoC.Configuration.ISettingsRequestor.
127    The implementation specifies a collection of required settings that should be present
128    in settings element.
129    Note, the type specified in type attribute is fully integrated into a dependency
130    injection framework. In other words, constructor parameters will be injected using
131    bindings specified in dependencyInjection element.
